'''Adam Savage''' (born [[July 15]], [[1960s#1967|1967]]) is an industrial design and special effects designer<ref name="Discovery">{{WebCite|url=http://www.discovery.com/tv-shows/mythbusters/bios/adam-savage|text=Adam Savage &#124; Mythbusters &#124; Discovery|work=discovery.com|archivedate=20171008022144}}</ref> who worked for [[Industrial Light & Magic|ILM]] building ships<ref name="SDCC">{{SW|url=news/undercover-mythbuster-adam-savage-goes-incognito-as-kylo-ren-sdcc-2016|text=Undercover Mythbuster: Adam Savage Goes Incognito as Kylo Ren at SDCC 2016 &ndash; Exclusive Interview!}}</ref> and miniature sets for [[Star Wars: Episode I The Phantom Menace|''The Phantom Menace'']] and [[Star Wars: Episode II Attack of the Clones|''Attack of the Clones'']].<ref name="Interview" /> During the production of Episode II, Savage nearly cameoed in the film itself when a stand-in for [[Temuera Morrison]] was needed to portray [[Jango Fett]]'s hand. Just as the scene was to be shot, however, Savage was called away to build something off the soundstage.<ref name="Insider 206">{{InsiderCite|206|Industry, Laughter, & Magical Times}}</ref>

He is most famous for co-hosting the [[Wikipedia:MythBusters|''MythBusters'']] show on the Discovery Channel, along with [[Jamie Hyneman]].<ref name="Discovery" /> In 2014, they hosted a ''[[MythBusters Star Wars Special]]'' episode. Savage voiced a member of the [[Galactic Empire/Legends|Galactic Empire]] along with Hyneman on ''[[Phineas and Ferb: Star Wars]]''.<ref name="phineas">{{WebCite|url=http://www.ign.com/articles/2014/07/18/phineas-and-ferb-star-wars-special-exclusive-image-reveal|text=IGN - Phineas & Ferb: Star Wars Special Exclusive Image Reveal|dateaccessed=2018-06-25|archivedate=20160603065901}}</ref>

